node.text:
Haider Ali wins gold for Pakistan! 🥇 

Team Pakistan have two athletes competing at the #Tokyo2020 Paralympic Games, that’s a high medal/athlete/country rate! 

“I'm happy to be the first Pakistani to get this medal in Pakistan history."

“This gold will be very important for Para sport in my country. I hope to be a role model for other people that have a disability."

Congratulations to Haider, victorious in the F37 discus throw. 

(Description: Ali smiles and holds up his bouquet 💐 on the podium).

#ParaAthletics #Paralympics #Tokyo2020 #Pakistan
